What you need to know:

This year, Treasury returned a 14 per cent VAT meaning prices will increase even further. Charcoal is here to stay.James Kimwemwe, a Kenya Forestry Research Institute (Kefri) charcoal expert, who has been involved in training CPAs says the producers are encouraged to use dry wood in modern kilns.The drum kiln is made from an ordinary oil drum with a short metal pipe that acts as a chimney. The chimney condenses smoke into wood vinegar which can be used as an organic pesticide and fertiliser.